{"id":78560,"title":"Suppressive therapy using azithromycin in 2 rare cases of recurrent staphylococcal infections.","abstract":"Recurrent staphylococcal skin and soft tissue infections may recur despite decontamination and multiple courses of antibiotic therapy and may dramatically impair the patient's quality of life. We report successful use of long-term azithromycin prophylaxis in a recurrent laryngitis and a scalp folliculitis due to methicillin-susceptible Staphylococcus aureus. ","date":"2014-04-15","categories":"Otorhinolaryngologic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24629578","annotations":[{"name":"Staphylococcus aureus","weight":0.86005,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Staphylococcus_aureus"},{"name":"Antibacterial","weight":0.826759,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antibacterial"},{"name":"Skin","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.75445,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Tissue (biology)","weight":0.644384,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tissue_(biology)"},{"name":"Staphylococcus","weight":0.573635,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Staphylococcus"},{"name":"Prophylaxis","weight":0.469957,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prophylaxis"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.360168,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Soft tissue","weight":0.296534,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soft_tissue"},{"name":"Azithromycin","weight":0.176208,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Azithromycin"},{"name":"Folliculitis","weight":0.160175,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Folliculitis"},{"name":"Quality of life","weight":0.128444,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quality_of_life"},{"name":"Scalp","weight":0.0377168,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sca